items.title: NTSB investigating deadly crash of plane owned by Mötley Crüe's Vince Neil
items.description: An investigation is underway into Monday's crash of a private jet owned by Mötley Crüe frontman Vince Neil in Scottsdale, Arizona. At least one person...

items.title: Canned tuna sold by major U.S. grocers recalled over botulism concerns
items.description: Certain tuna products may have defective lids that could lead to "a potentially fatal form of food poisoning," FDA notice states.

items.title: Shopify takes down Ye store selling swastika T-shirts
items.description: Shopify said Yeezy.com violated its policies by selling a shirt promoted by Ye, formerly known as Kanye West, emblazoned with a swastika.

items.title: Is it risky to open a CD with an online bank? What experts say
items.description: Online banks may offer better rates, but there are some potential drawbacks to take into account, too.

items.title: Vance warns EU against AI overregulation at summit in Paris
items.description: In his first international address, Vice President JD Vance also argued AI must remain free from "ideological bias."
